  47. (* notify_catch associates to each catch handler a callback
  48.    which will be passed the list of arguments of each
  49.    staticfail instruction pointing to that handler. This
  50.    allows transl_catch to observe concrete arguments passed to each
  51.    handler parameter and decide whether to unbox them accordingly.

  53.    Other ways to achieve the same result would be to either (1) traverse
  54.    the body of the catch block after translation (this would be costly
  55.    and could easily lead to quadratric behavior) or (2) return
  56.    a description of arguments passed to each catch handler as an extra
  57.    value to be threaded through all transl_* functions (this would be
  58.    quite heavy, and probably less efficient that the callback approach).
  59. *)

  459.   (* Primitives *)
  460.   | Uprim(prim, args, dbg) ->
  461.       begin match (simplif_primitive prim, args) with
  462.       | (Pread_symbol sym, []) ->
  463.           Cconst_symbol (sym, dbg)
  464.       | (Pmakeblock _, []) ->
  465.           assert false
  466.       | (Pmakeblock(tag, _mut, _kind), args) ->
  467.           make_alloc dbg tag (List.map (transl env) args)
  468.       | (Pccall prim, args) ->
  469.           transl_ccall env prim args dbg
  470.       | (Pduparray (kind, _), [Uprim (Pmakearray (kind', _), args, _dbg)]) ->
  471.           (* We arrive here in two cases:
  472.              1. When using Closure, all the time.
  473.              2. When using Flambda, if a float array longer than
  474.              [Translcore.use_dup_for_constant_arrays_bigger_than] turns out
  475.              to be non-constant.
  476.              If for some reason Flambda fails to lift a constant array we
  477.              could in theory also end up here.
  478.              Note that [kind] above is unconstrained, but with the current
  479.              state of [Translcore], we will in fact only get here with
  480.              [Pfloatarray]s. *)
  481.           assert (kind = kind');
  482.           transl_make_array dbg env kind args
  483.       | (Pduparray _, [arg]) ->
  484. ‌          let prim_obj_dup =
  485.             Primitive.simple ~name:"caml_obj_dup" ~arity:1 ~alloc:true
  486.           in
  487.           transl_ccall env prim_obj_dup [arg] dbg
  488.       | (Pmakearray _, []) ->
  489.           Misc.fatal_error "Pmakearray is not allowed for an empty array"
  490.       | (Pmakearray (kind, _), args) -> transl_make_array dbg env kind args
  491.       | (Pbigarrayref(unsafe, _num_dims, elt_kind, layout), arg1 :: argl) ->
  492. ‌          let elt =
  493.             bigarray_get unsafe elt_kind layout
  494.               (transl env arg1) (List.map (transl env) argl) dbg in
  495.           begin match elt_kind with
  496.             Pbigarray_float32 | Pbigarray_float64 -> box_float dbg elt
  497.           | Pbigarray_complex32 | Pbigarray_complex64 -> elt
  498.           | Pbigarray_int32 -> box_int dbg Pint32 elt
  499.           | Pbigarray_int64 -> box_int dbg Pint64 elt
  500.           | Pbigarray_native_int -> box_int dbg Pnativeint elt
  501.           | Pbigarray_caml_int -> tag_int elt dbg
  502.           | Pbigarray_sint8 | Pbigarray_uint8
  503.           | Pbigarray_sint16 | Pbigarray_uint16 -> tag_int elt dbg
  504.           | Pbigarray_unknown -> assert false
  505.           end
  506.       | (Pbigarrayset(unsafe, _num_dims, elt_kind, layout), arg1 :: argl) ->
  507. ‌          let (argidx, argnewval) = split_last argl in
  508.           return_unit dbg (bigarray_set unsafe elt_kind layout
  509.             (transl env arg1)
  510.             (List.map (transl env) argidx)
  511.             (match elt_kind with
  512.               Pbigarray_float32 | Pbigarray_float64 ->
  513.                 transl_unbox_float dbg env argnewval
  514.             | Pbigarray_complex32 | Pbigarray_complex64 -> transl env argnewval
  515.             | Pbigarray_int32 -> transl_unbox_int dbg env Pint32 argnewval
  516.             | Pbigarray_int64 -> transl_unbox_int dbg env Pint64 argnewval
  517.             | Pbigarray_native_int ->
  518.                 transl_unbox_int dbg env Pnativeint argnewval
  519.             | Pbigarray_caml_int ->
  520.                 untag_int (transl env argnewval) dbg
  521.             | Pbigarray_sint8 | Pbigarray_uint8
  522.             | Pbigarray_sint16 | Pbigarray_uint16 ->
  523.                 ignore_high_bit_int (untag_int (transl env argnewval) dbg)
  524.             | Pbigarray_unknown -> assert false)
  525.             dbg)
  526.       | (Pbigarraydim(n), [b]) ->
  527. ‌          let dim_ofs = 4 + n in
  528.           tag_int (Cop(mk_load_mut Word_int,
  529.             [field_address (transl env b) dim_ofs dbg],
  530.             dbg)) dbg
  531.       | (p, [arg]) ->
  532.           transl_prim_1 env p arg dbg
  533.       | (p, [arg1; arg2]) ->
  534.           transl_prim_2 env p arg1 arg2 dbg
  535.       | (p, [arg1; arg2; arg3]) ->
  536.           transl_prim_3 env p arg1 arg2 arg3 dbg
  537.       | (Pread_symbol _, _::_::_::_::_)
  538.       | (Pbigarrayset (_, _, _, _), [])
  539.       | (Pbigarrayref (_, _, _, _), [])
  540.       | ((Pbigarraydim _ | Pduparray (_, _)), ([] | _::_::_::_::_))
  541.         ->
  542.           fatal_error "Cmmgen.transl:prim, wrong arity"
  543.       | ((Pfield_computed|Psequand
  544.          | Prunstack | Pperform | Presume | Preperform
  545.          | Pdls_get
  546.          | Patomic_load _ | Patomic_exchange
  547.          | Patomic_cas | Patomic_fetch_add
  548.          | Psequor | Pnot | Pnegint | Paddint | Psubint
  549.          | Pmulint | Pandint | Porint | Pxorint | Plslint
  550.          | Plsrint | Pasrint | Pintoffloat | Pfloatofint
  551.          | Pnegfloat | Pabsfloat | Paddfloat | Psubfloat
  552.          | Pmulfloat | Pdivfloat | Pstringlength | Pstringrefu
  553.          | Pstringrefs | Pbyteslength | Pbytesrefu | Pbytessetu
  554.          | Pbytesrefs | Pbytessets | Pisint | Pisout
  555.          | Pbswap16 | Pint_as_pointer | Popaque | Pfield _
  556.          | Psetfield (_, _, _) | Psetfield_computed (_, _)
  557.          | Pfloatfield _ | Psetfloatfield (_, _) | Pduprecord (_, _)
  558.          | Praise _ | Pdivint _ | Pmodint _ | Pintcomp _ | Poffsetint _
  559.          | Pcompare_ints | Pcompare_floats | Pcompare_bints _
  560.          | Poffsetref _ | Pfloatcomp _ | Parraylength _
  561.          | Parrayrefu _ | Parraysetu _ | Parrayrefs _ | Parraysets _
  562.          | Pbintofint _ | Pintofbint _ | Pcvtbint (_, _) | Pnegbint _
  563.          | Paddbint _ | Psubbint _ | Pmulbint _ | Pdivbint _ | Pmodbint _
  564.          | Pandbint _ | Porbint _ | Pxorbint _ | Plslbint _ | Plsrbint _
  565.          | Pasrbint _ | Pbintcomp (_, _) | Pstring_load _ | Pbytes_load _
  566.          | Pbytes_set _ | Pbigstring_load _ | Pbigstring_set _
  567.          | Pbbswap _), _)
  568.         ->
  569.           fatal_error "Cmmgen.transl:prim"
  570.       end

  572.   (* Control structures *)
  573.   | Uswitch(arg, s, dbg) ->
  574.       (* As in the bytecode interpreter, only matching against constants
  575.          can be checked *)
  576.       if Array.length s.us_index_blocks = 0 then
  577.         make_switch
  578.           (untag_int (transl env arg) dbg)
  579.           s.us_index_consts
  580.           (Array.map (fun expr -> transl env expr, dbg) s.us_actions_consts)
  581.           dbg
  582.       else if Array.length s.us_index_consts = 0 then
  583.         bind "switch" (transl env arg) (fun arg ->
  584.           transl_switch dbg env (get_tag arg dbg)
  585.             s.us_index_blocks s.us_actions_blocks)
  586.       else
  587.         bind "switch" (transl env arg) (fun arg ->
  588.           Cifthenelse(
  589.           Cop(Cand, [arg; Cconst_int (1, dbg)], dbg),
  590.           dbg,
  591.           transl_switch dbg env
  592.             (untag_int arg dbg) s.us_index_consts s.us_actions_consts,
  593.           dbg,
  594.           transl_switch dbg env
  595.             (get_tag arg dbg) s.us_index_blocks s.us_actions_blocks,
  596.           dbg))
  597.   | Ustringswitch(arg,sw,d) ->
  598. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  599.       bind "switch" (transl env arg)
  600.         (fun arg ->
  601.           strmatch_compile dbg arg (Option.map (transl env) d)
  602.             (List.map (fun (s,act) -> s,transl env act) sw))
  603.   | Ustaticfail (nfail, args) ->
  604. ‌      let cargs = List.map (transl env) args in
  605.       notify_catch nfail env cargs;
  606.       Cexit (nfail, cargs)
  607.   | Ucatch(nfail, [], body, handler) ->
  608. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  609.       make_catch nfail (transl env body) (transl env handler) dbg
  610.   | Ucatch(nfail, ids, body, handler) ->
  611. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  612.       transl_catch env nfail ids body handler dbg
  613.   | Utrywith(body, exn, handler) ->
  614. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  615.       Ctrywith(transl env body, exn, transl env handler, dbg)
  616.   | Uifthenelse(cond, ifso, ifnot) ->
  617. ‌      let ifso_dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  618. ‌      let ifnot_dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  619. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  620. ‌      let ifso = transl env ifso in
  621. ‌      let ifnot = transl env ifnot in
  622. ‌      let approx =
  623.         match ifso, ifnot with
  624.         | Cconst_int (1, _), Cconst_int (3, _) -> Then_false_else_true
  625.         | Cconst_int (3, _), Cconst_int (1, _) -> Then_true_else_false
  626.         | _, _ -> Unknown
  627.       in
  628.       transl_if env approx dbg cond
  629.         ifso_dbg ifso ifnot_dbg ifnot
  630.   | Usequence(exp1, exp2) ->
  631.       Csequence(remove_unit(transl env exp1), transl env exp2)
  632.   | Uwhile(cond, body) ->
  633. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  634. ‌      let raise_num = next_raise_count () in
  635.       return_unit dbg
  636.         (ccatch
  637.            (raise_num, [],
  638.             create_loop(transl_if env Unknown dbg cond
  639.                     dbg (remove_unit(transl env body))
  640.                     dbg (Cexit (raise_num,[])))
  641.               dbg,
  642.             Ctuple [],
  643.             dbg))
  644.   | Ufor(id, low, high, dir, body) ->
  645. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  646. ‌      let tst = match dir with Upto -> Cgt   | Downto -> Clt in
  647. ‌      let inc = match dir with Upto -> Caddi | Downto -> Csubi in
  648. ‌      let raise_num = next_raise_count () in
  649. ‌      let id_prev = VP.create (V.create_local "*id_prev*") in
  650.       return_unit dbg
  651.         (Clet_mut
  652.            (id, typ_int, transl env low,
  653.             bind_nonvar "bound" (transl env high) (fun high ->
  654.               ccatch
  655.                 (raise_num, [],
  656.                  Cifthenelse
  657.                    (Cop(Ccmpi tst, [Cvar (VP.var id); high], dbg),
  658.                     dbg,
  659.                     Cexit (raise_num, []),
  660.                     dbg,
  661.                     create_loop
  662.                       (Csequence
  663.                          (remove_unit(transl env body),
  664.                          Clet(id_prev, Cvar (VP.var id),
  665.                           Csequence
  666.                             (Cassign(VP.var id,
  667.                                Cop(inc, [Cvar (VP.var id); Cconst_int (2, dbg)],
  668.                                  dbg)),
  669.                              Cifthenelse
  670.                                (Cop(Ccmpi Ceq, [Cvar (VP.var id_prev); high],
  671.                                   dbg),
  672.                                 dbg, Cexit (raise_num,[]),
  673.                                 dbg, Ctuple [],
  674.                                 dbg)))))
  675.                       dbg,
  676.                    dbg),
  677.                  Ctuple [],
  678.                  dbg))))
  679.   | Uassign(id, exp) ->
  680. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  681. ‌      let cexp = transl env exp in
  682.       begin match is_unboxed_id id env with
  683.       | None ->
  684.           return_unit dbg (Cassign(id, cexp))
  685.       | Some (unboxed_id, bn) ->
  686.           return_unit dbg (Cassign(unboxed_id, unbox_number dbg bn cexp))
  687.       end
  688.   | Uunreachable ->
  689. ‌      let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  690.       Cop(mk_load_mut Word_int, [Cconst_int (0, dbg)], dbg)

  692. ‌and transl_catch env nfail ids body handler dbg =
  693.   let ids = List.map (fun (id, kind) -> (id, kind, ref No_result)) ids in
  694.   (* Translate the body, and while doing so, collect the "unboxing type" for
  695.      each argument.  *)
  696.   let report args =
  697.     List.iter2
  698.       (fun (_id, kind, u) c ->
  699.          let strict =
  700.            match kind with
  701.            | Pfloatval | Pboxedintval _ -> false
  702.            | Pintval | Pgenval -> true
  703.          in
  704.          u := join_unboxed_number_kind ~strict !u
  705.              (is_unboxed_number_cmm ~strict c)
  706.       )
  707.       ids args
  708.   in
  709.   let env_body = add_notify_catch nfail report env in
  710.   let body = transl env_body body in
  711.   let new_env, rewrite, ids =
  712.     List.fold_right
  713.       (fun (id, _kind, u) (env, rewrite, ids) ->
  714.          match !u with
  715.          | No_unboxing | Boxed (_, true) | No_result ->
  716.              env,
  717.              (fun x -> x) :: rewrite,
  718.              (id, Cmm.typ_val) :: ids
  719.          | Boxed (bn, false) ->
  720.              let unboxed_id = V.create_local (VP.name id) in
  721.              add_unboxed_id (VP.var id) unboxed_id bn env,
  722.              (unbox_number Debuginfo.none bn) :: rewrite,
  723.              (VP.create unboxed_id, typ_of_boxed_number bn) :: ids
  724.       )
  725.       ids (env, [], [])
  726.   in
  727.   if env == new_env then
  728.     (* No unboxing *)
  729.     ccatch (nfail, ids, body, transl env handler, dbg)
  730.   else
  731.     (* allocate new "nfail" to catch errors more easily *)
  732.     let new_nfail = next_raise_count () in
  733.     let body =
  734.       (* Rewrite the body to unbox the call sites *)
  735.       let rec aux e =
  736.         match Cmm.map_shallow aux e with
  737.         | Cexit (n, el) when n = nfail ->
  738.             Cexit (new_nfail, List.map2 (fun f e -> f e) rewrite el)
  739.         | c -> c
  740.       in
  741.       aux body
  742.     in
  743.     ccatch (new_nfail, ids, body, transl new_env handler, dbg)

  745. and transl_make_array dbg env kind args =
  746.   match kind with
  747.   | Pgenarray ->
  748.       Cop(Cextcall("caml_make_array", typ_val, [], true),
  749.           [make_alloc dbg 0 (List.map (transl env) args)], dbg)
  750.   | Paddrarray | Pintarray ->
  751.       make_alloc dbg 0 (List.map (transl env) args)
  752.   | Pfloatarray ->
  753.       make_float_alloc dbg Obj.double_array_tag
  754.                       (List.map (transl_unbox_float dbg env) args)

  756. and transl_ccall env prim args dbg =
  757.   let transl_arg native_repr arg =
  758.     match native_repr with
  759.     | Same_as_ocaml_repr ->
  760.         (XInt, transl env arg)
  761.     | Unboxed_float ->
  762.         (XFloat, transl_unbox_float dbg env arg)
  763.     | Unboxed_integer bi ->
  764.         let xty =
  765.           match bi with
  766.           | Pnativeint -> XInt
  767.           | Pint32 -> XInt32
  768.           | Pint64 -> XInt64 in
  769.         (xty, transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg)
  770.     | Untagged_int ->
  771.         (XInt, untag_int (transl env arg) dbg)
  772.   in
  773.   let rec transl_args native_repr_args args =
  774.     match native_repr_args, args with
  775.     | [], args ->
  776.         (* We don't require the two lists to be of the same length as
  777.            [default_prim] always sets the arity to [0]. *)
  778.         (List.map (fun _ -> XInt) args, List.map (transl env) args)
  779.     | _, [] ->
  780.         assert false
  781.     | native_repr :: native_repr_args, arg :: args ->
  782.         let (ty1, arg') = transl_arg native_repr arg in
  783.         let (tys, args') = transl_args native_repr_args args in
  784.         (ty1 :: tys, arg' :: args')
  785.   in
  786.   let typ_res, wrap_result =
  787.     match prim.prim_native_repr_res with
  788.     | Same_as_ocaml_repr -> (typ_val, fun x -> x)
  789.     | Unboxed_float -> (typ_float, box_float dbg)
  790.     | Unboxed_integer bi -> (typ_int, box_int dbg bi)
  791.     | Untagged_int -> (typ_int, (fun i -> tag_int i dbg))
  792.   in
  793.   let typ_args, args = transl_args prim.prim_native_repr_args args in
  794.   wrap_result
  795.     (Cop(Cextcall(Primitive.native_name prim,
  796.                   typ_res, typ_args, prim.prim_alloc), args, dbg))

  798. and transl_prim_1 env p arg dbg =
  799.   match p with
  800.   (* Generic operations *)
  801.     Popaque ->
  802.       opaque (transl env arg) dbg
  803.   (* Heap operations *)
  804.   | Pfield(n, _, _) ->
  805.       get_field env (transl env arg) n dbg
  806.   | Pfloatfield n ->
  807.       let ptr = transl env arg in
  808.       box_float dbg (floatfield n ptr dbg)
  809.   | Pint_as_pointer ->
  810.       int_as_pointer (transl env arg) dbg
  811.   (* Exceptions *)
  812.   | Praise rkind ->
  813.       raise_prim rkind (transl env arg) dbg
  814.   (* Integer operations *)
  815.   | Pnegint ->
  816.       negint (transl env arg) dbg
  817.   | Poffsetint n ->
  818.       offsetint n (transl env arg) dbg
  819.   | Poffsetref n ->
  820.       offsetref n (transl env arg) dbg
  821.   (* Floating-point operations *)
  822.   | Pfloatofint ->
  823.       box_float dbg (Cop(Cfloatofint, [untag_int(transl env arg) dbg], dbg))
  824.   | Pintoffloat ->
  825.      tag_int(Cop(Cintoffloat, [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg], dbg)) dbg
  826.   | Pnegfloat ->
  827.       box_float dbg (Cop(Cnegf, [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg], dbg))
  828.   | Pabsfloat ->
  829.       box_float dbg (Cop(Cabsf, [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg], dbg))
  830.   (* String operations *)
  831.   | Pstringlength | Pbyteslength ->
  832.       tag_int(string_length (transl env arg) dbg) dbg
  833.   (* Array operations *)
  834.   | Parraylength kind ->
  835.       arraylength kind (transl env arg) dbg
  836.   (* Boolean operations *)
  837.   | Pnot ->
  838.       transl_if env Then_false_else_true
  839.         dbg arg
  840.         dbg (Cconst_int (1, dbg))
  841.         dbg (Cconst_int (3, dbg))
  842.   (* Test integer/block *)
  843.   | Pisint ->
  844.       tag_int(Cop(Cand, [transl env arg; Cconst_int (1, dbg)], dbg)) dbg
  845.   (* Boxed integers *)
  846.   | Pbintofint bi ->
  847.       box_int dbg bi (untag_int (transl env arg) dbg)
  848.   | Pintofbint bi ->
  849.       tag_int (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg) dbg
  850.   | Pcvtbint(bi1, bi2) ->
  851.       box_int dbg bi2 (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi1 arg)
  852.   | Pnegbint bi ->
  853.       box_int dbg bi
  854.         (Cop(Csubi, [Cconst_int (0, dbg); transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg],
  855.           dbg))
  856.   | Pbbswap bi ->
  857.       box_int dbg bi (bbswap bi (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg) dbg)
  858.   | Pbswap16 ->
  859.       tag_int (bswap16 (ignore_high_bit_int (untag_int
  860.         (transl env arg) dbg)) dbg) dbg
  861.   | Pperform ->
  862.       let cont = make_alloc dbg Obj.cont_tag [int_const dbg 0] in
  863.       Cop(Capply typ_val,
  864.        [Cconst_symbol ("caml_perform", dbg); transl env arg; cont],
  865.        dbg)
  866.   | Pdls_get ->
  867.       Cop(Cdls_get, [transl env arg], dbg)
  868.   | Patomic_load {immediate_or_pointer = Immediate} ->
  869.       Cop(mk_load_atomic Word_int, [transl env arg], dbg)
  870.   | Patomic_load {immediate_or_pointer = Pointer} ->
  871.       Cop(mk_load_atomic Word_val, [transl env arg], dbg)
  872.   | (Pfield_computed | Psequand | Psequor
  873.     | Prunstack | Presume | Preperform
  874.     | Patomic_exchange | Patomic_cas | Patomic_fetch_add
  875.     | Paddint | Psubint | Pmulint | Pandint
  876.     | Porint | Pxorint | Plslint | Plsrint | Pasrint
  877.     | Paddfloat | Psubfloat | Pmulfloat | Pdivfloat
  878.     | Pstringrefu | Pstringrefs | Pbytesrefu | Pbytessetu
  879.     | Pbytesrefs | Pbytessets | Pisout | Pread_symbol _
  880.     | Pmakeblock (_, _, _) | Psetfield (_, _, _) | Psetfield_computed (_, _)
  881.     | Psetfloatfield (_, _) | Pduprecord (_, _) | Pccall _ | Pdivint _
  882.     | Pmodint _ | Pintcomp _ | Pfloatcomp _ | Pmakearray (_, _)
  883.     | Pcompare_ints | Pcompare_floats | Pcompare_bints _
  884.     | Pduparray (_, _) | Parrayrefu _ | Parraysetu _
  885.     | Parrayrefs _ | Parraysets _ | Paddbint _ | Psubbint _ | Pmulbint _
  886.     | Pdivbint _ | Pmodbint _ | Pandbint _ | Porbint _ | Pxorbint _
  887.     | Plslbint _ | Plsrbint _ | Pasrbint _ | Pbintcomp (_, _)
  888.     | Pbigarrayref (_, _, _, _) | Pbigarrayset (_, _, _, _)
  889.     | Pbigarraydim _ | Pstring_load _ | Pbytes_load _ | Pbytes_set _
  890.     | Pbigstring_load _ | Pbigstring_set _)
  891.     ->
  892.       fatal_errorf "Cmmgen.transl_prim_1: %a"
  893.         Printclambda_primitives.primitive p

  895. and transl_prim_2 env p arg1 arg2 dbg =
  896.   match p with
  897.   (* Heap operations *)
  898.   | Pfield_computed ->
  899.       addr_array_ref (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  900.   | Psetfield(n, ptr, init) ->
  901.       setfield n ptr init (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  902.   | Psetfloatfield (n, init) ->
  903.       let ptr = transl env arg1 in
  904.       let float_val = transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2 in
  905.       setfloatfield n init ptr float_val dbg

  907.   (* Boolean operations *)
  908.   | Psequand ->
  909.       let dbg' = Debuginfo.none in
  910.       transl_sequand env Then_true_else_false
  911.         dbg arg1
  912.         dbg' arg2
  913.         dbg (Cconst_int (3, dbg))
  914.         dbg' (Cconst_int (1, dbg))
  915.       (* let id = V.create_local "res1" in
  916.       Clet(id, transl env arg1,
  917.            Cifthenelse(test_bool dbg (Cvar id), transl env arg2, Cvar id)) *)
  918.   | Psequor ->
  919.       let dbg' = Debuginfo.none in
  920.       transl_sequor env Then_true_else_false
  921.         dbg arg1
  922.         dbg' arg2
  923.         dbg (Cconst_int (3, dbg))
  924.         dbg' (Cconst_int (1, dbg))
  925.   (* Integer operations *)
  926.   | Paddint ->
  927.       add_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  928.   | Psubint ->
  929.       sub_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  930.   | Pmulint ->
  931.       mul_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  932.   | Pdivint is_safe ->
  933.       div_int_caml is_safe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  934.   | Pmodint is_safe ->
  935.       mod_int_caml is_safe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  936.   | Pandint ->
  937.       and_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  938.   | Porint ->
  939.       or_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  940.   | Pxorint ->
  941.       xor_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  942.   | Plslint ->
  943.       lsl_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  944.   | Plsrint ->
  945.       lsr_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  946.   | Pasrint ->
  947.       asr_int_caml (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  948.   | Pintcomp cmp ->
  949.       int_comp_caml cmp (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  950.   | Pcompare_ints ->
  951.       (* Compare directly on tagged ints *)
  952.       mk_compare_ints dbg (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2)
  953.   | Pcompare_bints bi ->
  954.       let a1 = transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg1 in
  955.       let a2 = transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg2 in
  956.       mk_compare_ints dbg a1 a2
  957.   | Pcompare_floats ->
  958.       let a1 = transl_unbox_float dbg env arg1 in
  959.       let a2 = transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2 in
  960.       mk_compare_floats dbg a1 a2
  961.   | Pisout ->
  962.       transl_isout (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  963.   (* Float operations *)
  964.   | Paddfloat ->
  965.       box_float dbg (Cop(Caddf,
  966.                     [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg1;
  967.                      transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2],
  968.                     dbg))
  969.   | Psubfloat ->
  970.       box_float dbg (Cop(Csubf,
  971.                     [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg1;
  972.                      transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2],
  973.                     dbg))
  974.   | Pmulfloat ->
  975.       box_float dbg (Cop(Cmulf,
  976.                     [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg1;
  977.                      transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2],
  978.                     dbg))
  979.   | Pdivfloat ->
  980.       box_float dbg (Cop(Cdivf,
  981.                     [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg1;
  982.                      transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2],
  983.                     dbg))
  984.   | Pfloatcomp cmp ->
  985.       tag_int(Cop(Ccmpf cmp,
  986.                   [transl_unbox_float dbg env arg1;
  987.                    transl_unbox_float dbg env arg2],
  988.                   dbg)) dbg

  990.   (* String operations *)
  991.   | Pstringrefu | Pbytesrefu ->
  992.       stringref_unsafe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  993.   | Pstringrefs | Pbytesrefs ->
  994.       stringref_safe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  995.   | Pstring_load(size, unsafe) | Pbytes_load(size, unsafe) ->
  996.       string_load size unsafe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  997.   | Pbigstring_load(size, unsafe) ->
  998.       bigstring_load size unsafe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg

  1000.   (* Array operations *)
  1001.   | Parrayrefu kind ->
  1002.       arrayref_unsafe kind (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg
  1003.   | Parrayrefs kind ->
  1004.       arrayref_safe kind (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) dbg

  1006.   (* Boxed integers *)
  1007.   | Paddbint bi ->
  1008.       box_int dbg bi (add_int
  1009.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1)
  1010.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg2) dbg)
  1011.   | Psubbint bi ->
  1012.       box_int dbg bi (sub_int
  1013.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1)
  1014.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg2) dbg)
  1015.   | Pmulbint bi ->
  1016.       box_int dbg bi (mul_int
  1017.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1)
  1018.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg2) dbg)
  1019.   | Pdivbint { size = bi; is_safe } ->
  1020.       box_int dbg bi (safe_div_bi is_safe
  1021.                       (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg1)
  1022.                       (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg2)
  1023.                       bi dbg)
  1024.   | Pmodbint { size = bi; is_safe } ->
  1025.       box_int dbg bi (safe_mod_bi is_safe
  1026.                       (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg1)
  1027.                       (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg2)
  1028.                       bi dbg)
  1029.   | Pandbint bi ->
  1030.       box_int dbg bi (Cop(Cand,
  1031.                      [transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1;
  1032.                       transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg2], dbg))
  1033.   | Porbint bi ->
  1034.       box_int dbg bi (Cop(Cor,
  1035.                      [transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1;
  1036.                       transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg2], dbg))
  1037.   | Pxorbint bi ->
  1038.       box_int dbg bi (Cop(Cxor,
  1039.                      [transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1;
  1040.                       transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg2], dbg))
  1041.   | Plslbint bi ->
  1042.       box_int dbg bi (lsl_int
  1043.                         (transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi arg1)
  1044.                         (untag_int(transl env arg2) dbg) dbg)
  1045.   | Plsrbint bi ->
  1046.       box_int dbg bi (lsr_int
  1047.                         (make_unsigned_int bi (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg1)
  1048.                                         dbg)
  1049.                         (untag_int(transl env arg2) dbg) dbg)
  1050.   | Pasrbint bi ->
  1051.       box_int dbg bi (asr_int
  1052.                         (transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg1)
  1053.                         (untag_int(transl env arg2) dbg) dbg)
  1054.   | Pbintcomp(bi, cmp) ->
  1055.       tag_int (Cop(Ccmpi cmp,
  1056.                      [transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg1;
  1057.                       transl_unbox_int dbg env bi arg2], dbg)) dbg
  1058.   | Patomic_exchange ->
  1059.      Cop (Cextcall ("caml_atomic_exchange", typ_val, [], false),
  1060.           [transl env arg1; transl env arg2], dbg)
  1061.   | Patomic_fetch_add ->
  1062.      Cop (Cextcall ("caml_atomic_fetch_add", typ_int, [], false),
  1063.           [transl env arg1; transl env arg2], dbg)
  1064.   | Prunstack | Pperform | Presume | Preperform | Pdls_get
  1065.   | Patomic_cas | Patomic_load _
  1066.   | Pnot | Pnegint | Pintoffloat | Pfloatofint | Pnegfloat
  1067.   | Pabsfloat | Pstringlength | Pbyteslength | Pbytessetu | Pbytessets
  1068.   | Pisint | Pbswap16 | Pint_as_pointer | Popaque | Pread_symbol _
  1069.   | Pmakeblock (_, _, _) | Pfield _ | Psetfield_computed (_, _) | Pfloatfield _
  1070.   | Pduprecord (_, _) | Pccall _ | Praise _ | Poffsetint _ | Poffsetref _
  1071.   | Pmakearray (_, _) | Pduparray (_, _) | Parraylength _ | Parraysetu _
  1072.   | Parraysets _ | Pbintofint _ | Pintofbint _ | Pcvtbint (_, _)
  1073.   | Pnegbint _ | Pbigarrayref (_, _, _, _) | Pbigarrayset (_, _, _, _)
  1074.   | Pbigarraydim _ | Pbytes_set _ | Pbigstring_set _ | Pbbswap _
  1075.     ->
  1076.       fatal_errorf "Cmmgen.transl_prim_2: %a"
  1077.         Printclambda_primitives.primitive p

  1079. and transl_prim_3 env p arg1 arg2 arg3 dbg =
  1080.   match p with
  1081.   (* Heap operations *)
  1082.   | Psetfield_computed(ptr, init) ->
  1083.       setfield_computed ptr init
  1084.         (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) (transl env arg3) dbg
  1085.   (* String operations *)
  1086.   | Pbytessetu ->
  1087.       bytesset_unsafe
  1088.         (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) (transl env arg3) dbg
  1089.   | Pbytessets ->
  1090.       bytesset_safe
  1091.         (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) (transl env arg3) dbg

  1093.   (* Array operations *)
  1094.   | Parraysetu kind ->
  1095.       let newval =
  1096.         match kind with
  1097.         | Pfloatarray -> transl_unbox_float dbg env arg3
  1098.         | _ -> transl env arg3
  1099.       in
  1100.       arrayset_unsafe kind (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) newval dbg
  1101.   | Parraysets kind ->
  1102.       let newval =
  1103.         match kind with
  1104.         | Pfloatarray -> transl_unbox_float dbg env arg3
  1105.         | _ -> transl env arg3
  1106.       in
  1107.       arrayset_safe kind (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2) newval dbg

  1109.   | Pbytes_set(size, unsafe) ->
  1110.       bytes_set size unsafe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2)
  1111.         (transl_unbox_sized size dbg env arg3) dbg

  1113.   | Pbigstring_set(size, unsafe) ->
  1114.       bigstring_set size unsafe (transl env arg1) (transl env arg2)
  1115.         (transl_unbox_sized size dbg env arg3) dbg

  1117.   | Patomic_cas ->
  1118.      Cop (Cextcall ("caml_atomic_cas", typ_int, [], false),
  1119.           [transl env arg1; transl env arg2; transl env arg3], dbg)

  1121.   (* Effects *)
  1122.   | Presume ->
  1123.       Cop (Capply typ_val,
  1124.            [Cconst_symbol ("caml_resume", dbg);
  1125.            transl env arg1; transl env arg2; transl env arg3],
  1126.            dbg)

  1128.   | Prunstack ->
  1129.       Cop (Capply typ_val,
  1130.            [Cconst_symbol ("caml_runstack", dbg);
  1131.            transl env arg1; transl env arg2; transl env arg3],
  1132.            dbg)

  1134.   | Preperform ->
  1135.       Cop (Capply typ_val,
  1136.            [Cconst_symbol ("caml_reperform", dbg);
  1137.            transl env arg1; transl env arg2; transl env arg3],
  1138.            dbg)

  1140.   | Pperform | Pdls_get
  1141.   | Patomic_exchange | Patomic_fetch_add | Patomic_load _
  1142.   | Pfield_computed | Psequand | Psequor | Pnot | Pnegint | Paddint
  1143.   | Psubint | Pmulint | Pandint | Porint | Pxorint | Plslint | Plsrint | Pasrint
  1144.   | Pintoffloat | Pfloatofint | Pnegfloat | Pabsfloat | Paddfloat | Psubfloat
  1145.   | Pmulfloat | Pdivfloat | Pstringlength | Pstringrefu | Pstringrefs
  1146.   | Pbyteslength | Pbytesrefu | Pbytesrefs | Pisint | Pisout
  1147.   | Pbswap16 | Pint_as_pointer | Popaque | Pread_symbol _ | Pmakeblock (_, _, _)
  1148.   | Pfield _ | Psetfield (_, _, _) | Pfloatfield _ | Psetfloatfield (_, _)
  1149.   | Pduprecord (_, _) | Pccall _ | Praise _ | Pdivint _ | Pmodint _ | Pintcomp _
  1150.   | Pcompare_ints | Pcompare_floats | Pcompare_bints _
  1151.   | Poffsetint _ | Poffsetref _ | Pfloatcomp _ | Pmakearray (_, _)
  1152.   | Pduparray (_, _) | Parraylength _ | Parrayrefu _ | Parrayrefs _
  1153.   | Pbintofint _ | Pintofbint _ | Pcvtbint (_, _) | Pnegbint _ | Paddbint _
  1154.   | Psubbint _ | Pmulbint _ | Pdivbint _ | Pmodbint _ | Pandbint _ | Porbint _
  1155.   | Pxorbint _ | Plslbint _ | Plsrbint _ | Pasrbint _ | Pbintcomp (_, _)
  1156.   | Pbigarrayref (_, _, _, _) | Pbigarrayset (_, _, _, _) | Pbigarraydim _
  1157.   | Pstring_load _ | Pbytes_load _ | Pbigstring_load _ | Pbbswap _
  1158.     ->
  1159.       fatal_errorf "Cmmgen.transl_prim_3: %a"
  1160.         Printclambda_primitives.primitive p

  1162. and transl_unbox_float dbg env exp =
  1163.   unbox_float dbg (transl env exp)

  1165. and transl_unbox_int dbg env bi exp =
  1166.   unbox_int dbg bi (transl env exp)

  1168. (* transl_unbox_int, but may return garbage in upper bits *)
  1169. and transl_unbox_int_low dbg env bi e =
  1170.   let e = transl_unbox_int dbg env bi e in
  1171.   if bi = Pint32 then low_32 dbg e else e

  1173. and transl_unbox_sized size dbg env exp =
  1174.   match size with
  1175.   | Sixteen ->
  1176.      ignore_high_bit_int (untag_int (transl env exp) dbg)
  1177.   | Thirty_two -> transl_unbox_int dbg env Pint32 exp
  1178.   | Sixty_four -> transl_unbox_int dbg env Pint64 exp

  1180. and transl_let env str kind id exp transl_body =
  1181.   let dbg = Debuginfo.none in
  1182.   let cexp = transl env exp in
  1183.   let unboxing =
  1184.     (* If [id] is a mutable variable (introduced to eliminate a local
  1185.        reference) and it contains a type of unboxable numbers, then
  1186.        force unboxing.  Indeed, if not boxed, each assignment to the variable
  1187.        might require some boxing, but such local references are often
  1188.        used in loops and we really want to avoid repeated boxing. *)
  1189.     match str, kind with
  1190.     | Mutable, Pfloatval ->
  1191.         Boxed (Boxed_float dbg, false)
  1192.     | Mutable, Pboxedintval bi ->
  1193.         Boxed (Boxed_integer (bi, dbg), false)
  1194.     | _, (Pfloatval | Pboxedintval _) ->
  1195.         (* It would be safe to always unbox in this case, but
  1196.            we do it only if this indeed allows us to get rid of
  1197.            some allocations in the bound expression. *)
  1198.         is_unboxed_number_cmm ~strict:false cexp
  1199.     | _, Pgenval ->
  1200.         (* Here we don't know statically that the bound expression
  1201.            evaluates to an unboxable number type.  We need to be stricter
  1202.            and ensure that all possible branches in the expression
  1203.            return a boxed value (of the same kind).  Indeed, with GADTs,
  1204.            different branches could return different types. *)
  1205.         is_unboxed_number_cmm ~strict:true cexp
  1206.     | _, Pintval ->
  1207.         No_unboxing
  1208.   in
  1209.   match unboxing with
  1210.   | No_unboxing | Boxed (_, true) | No_result ->
  1211.       (* N.B. [body] must still be traversed even if [exp] will never return:
  1212.          there may be constant closures inside that need lifting out. *)
  1213.       begin match str, kind with
  1214.       | Immutable, _ -> Clet(id, cexp, transl_body env)
  1215.       | Mutable, Pintval -> Clet_mut(id, typ_int, cexp, transl_body env)
  1216.       | Mutable, _ -> Clet_mut(id, typ_val, cexp, transl_body env)
  1217.       end
  1218.   | Boxed (boxed_number, false) ->
  1219.       let unboxed_id = V.create_local (VP.name id) in
  1220.       let v = VP.create unboxed_id in
  1221.       let cexp = unbox_number dbg boxed_number cexp in
  1222.       let body =
  1223.         transl_body (add_unboxed_id (VP.var id) unboxed_id boxed_number env) in
  1224.       begin match str, boxed_number with
  1225.       | Immutable, _ -> Clet (v, cexp, body)
  1226.       | Mutable, bn -> Clet_mut (v, typ_of_boxed_number bn, cexp, body)
  1227.       end

  1229. and make_catch ncatch body handler dbg = match body with
  1230. | Cexit (nexit,[]) when nexit=ncatch -> handler
  1231. | _ ->  ccatch (ncatch, [], body, handler, dbg)

  1233. and is_shareable_cont exp =
  1234.   match exp with
  1235.   | Cexit (_,[]) -> true
  1236.   | _ -> false

  1238. and make_shareable_cont dbg mk exp =
  1239.   if is_shareable_cont exp then mk exp
  1240.   else begin
  1241.     let nfail = next_raise_count () in
  1242.     make_catch
  1243.       nfail
  1244.       (mk (Cexit (nfail,[])))
  1245.       exp
  1246.       dbg
  1247.   end

  1249. and transl_if env (approx : then_else)
  1250.       (dbg : Debuginfo.t) cond
  1251.       (then_dbg : Debuginfo.t) then_
